# Workflow Rule

- Start from a plan, an existing task spec, or a clearly scoped task request.
- If a plan or phase slice exists, derive or refine one or more task specs before editing. Use `skills/plan-to-spec.md` by default.
- Do not require a separate written plan document when the plan is already clear enough to derive specs.
- If iterating within the same reviewable slice, refine the existing spec instead of creating parallel docs.
- If the primary outcome, boundary, or validation path changes, create a new dated spec before editing.
- Prefer one task spec with one primary reviewable outcome and a short checklist.
- A tiny task may skip spec creation only when the request is already effectively spec-complete and trivially narrow.
- Implement only after the task boundary is clear.
- Validate explicitly after implementation.
- Write back stable facts only when justified.
- Promote repeated workflows into skills when they stabilize.
